description: Less is more on our version of this classic Italian Margherita-fresh Roma tomato, roasted garlic, tons of basil and our impeccable creamy Mozzarella. (S)

name: Spinach Pie
description: Mounds of fresh spinach with Feta cheese, sundried tomatoes, roasted garlic, pine nuts, and a hint of oregano over an olive oil glaze. Imported Kalamata olives if you wish. A pizza you'll crave. (O)

name: Bbq Chicken
description: Grilled chicken tossed in Sweet Baby Ray's award-winning BBQ sauce, paired with red onion and garnished with fresh cilantro. The urban cowboy's dream. (O)

name: The B.l.t.
description: Club sandwich lovers everywhere will filp for this one! The HomeMade BLT combines hickory-smoked bacon, fresh spinach, aged Parmigiano-Reggiano and a bit of fresh garlic over a layer of our delicious tomato sauce. Robust and truly satisfying, bringing home the bacon has never tasted quite this good. (S)

name: Wild Mushroom
description: Earthy wild mushrooms meld perfectly with rich creamy Fontinella, accented by fresh thyme. Complex and amazing. (O)

name: Four Cheese
description: Heavenly melding of strong and subtle-Asiago, Fontinella, Wisconsin Mozzarella, and Ricotta. A gastronomic experience not to be taken lightly. (S)

name: Sausage and Carmelized Onion
description: Already our signature pie. Our all-natural Italian sausage, sweet carmelized onion, Asiago cheese and a dash of sage top a bed of HomeMade cheeses and our incredible ruby tomato sauce. (S)

name: Savory Pie
description: Inspired by the flavors of Provence: Roasted red peppers, marinated artichokes, carmelized onions, our mild Chèvre and imported Kalamata olives. (O)

name: The Georgia
description: Cumin-scented Santa Fe chicken sausage is tempered by the mellow crunch of poblano peppers and finished with smooth Ricotta cheese. Where fierce passion and cool objectivity coincide--like a ride through the New Mexico landscape. (S)14.25

name: Quattro Stagioni
description: HomeMade tweaks an Italian classic uniting prosciutto, artichokes, wild mushrooms, Kalamata olives, Fontinella cheese and fresh thyme. Take a bite and imagine the winding streets of Florence... the rocky beaches of the Amalfi Coast--Bellissimo! (S)

name: Cutie Pie

description: just the meat, w/ dill pickle, cole slaw, and stilton mac & cheese

description: from black earth farms; cooked in sierra nevada porter-horseradish broth, w/ braised collard greens, celery root purèe, fried goose point oyster, pickled pearl onions

name: Rabbit & Dumplings
description: gunthorp farms rabbit in barbãr winter bock broth, w/ cauliflower, pearl onions, carrots & brussel sprouts

name: Pan-Roasted Poussin
description: w/ turnip-potato purée, savoy cabbage, carrots, bacon-mustard jus

name: Spice-Crusted Sturgeon
description: w/ roasted baby turnips, sauteed turnip greens, & shallot-beet marmalade

name: Squash "Wellington"
description: roasted butternut squash & mushroom duxelle wrapped in crispy phyllo dough; w/ glazed cippolini onions, brussel sprouts & mushroom "bordelaise" sauce

name: Clos Normand - Brut Cider
description: refreshing, light, dry; lightly carbonated; very fresh apple taste

name: Domaine Dupont - Cidre Bouche Fermier
description: this exceptional cider is from the 6000-tree dupont orchard, family-owned since 1837. 6 types of apples, picked manually at 3 stages of ripeness; proportions of the varieties is exact. slow-fermented, naturally carbonated, and unfiltered. full-bodied, complex and woody. very small quantities produced

name: Christian Drouin - Poiré Pear Cider
description: from normandy. blend of 5 varieties of estate-grown pears

name: Sarasola - Basque Cider
description: unfiltered, unpasteurized & non-carbonated. made from the tart apples of astigarraga. not sweet, lots of real fresh sour apple aroma & flavor. those that love gueuze lambic will go for this in a big way. a thirst-quenching palate quencher

name: Original Sin - Cider
description: made w/ n.y. state granny smith apples. not too sweet, lightly carbonated & a bit tart

name: Samuel Smith - Organic Cider (Imperial Pint)
description: crisp, clean & dry. uk & us certified organic

name: Jadwiga - Miod Pitney Poltorak
description: aged in oak for 5 years!

name: Blanc De Fleur
description: dry mead made w/ local wild flower honey

name: Blueberry Nectar
description: made w/ local honey & 20% michigan blueberries

name: Brugs Tripel
description: hazy golden color, sweet malt, spice, and lots of yeast. a bit spritzy

name: Barbar
description: golden blond honey ale. easy-drinking w/well-hidden alcohol (so watch out!) nicely sweet, floral, fruity & spicy; honey flavor becomes more evident as it warms; nice contrasting acidic finish

name: Gran Cru
description: bottle-conditioned blend of ales aged in oak tuns of various sizes, each imparting its individual character. sweet, acidic & fruity with sour grape background

name: Gluten-Free Tripel
description: green’s beers contain none of the following: wheat and or soya beans, milk, lactose, nuts, celery, mustard, sesame seeds, sulphur dioxide, sulfites. called an abbey tripel but made w/sorghum, buckwheat & millet. light-to-med-bodied & fizzy. stonefruity, apple-y w/alcohol heat; light malt sweetness

name: Vuuve
description: flemish for "five"; brewed by johan brandt for the 5th anniversary of his "rainbow" brewery. 60% barley and 40% wheat, plus hops, coriander, and organic orange peel. fruity, spicy, citrusy, prickly on the palate. strong wit beer

name: Wostyntje Mustard Beer
description: made w/90% pilsner malt, kent goldings & challenger hops, crushed torhout mustard seeds (imparting a unique bitterish finish) and dark & light candy sugars

name: 'T Smisje BB Bourgondier
description: a highlight of the 2002 "24 hours of beer" in antwerp. dark bottle-conditioned ale ale brewed w/valerian & lemon balm

name: The Bitter Truth
description: from a brewer who likes to brew untraditional beers in the traditional way! category-defying beers include this fruity-nosed, full-bodied and bitter-finishing beer that might remind one of a california triple ipa with a belgian twist.

name: Wittekerke
description: wit beer from bavik, w. flanders. tart lemon flavor w/light coriander & clove notes

name: Hoegaarden
description: the original white beer, brewed since the 15th century. wheat, coriander & citrus notes combine in this natu rally cloudy, very refreshing, distinctive beer

name: Blonde
description: honey, hops, bread and yeast flavors all get their due. nice balance

name: Lambrucha
description: brewed by detroch in wambeek. combining hand-selected house lambics that are at least 1 year old & batches of specially brewed organic kombucha fermented tea. both the tea and the lambic beer contain strains of brettanomyces & pediococcus, so this is a natural marriage of flavors

name: Lachouffe
description: strong golden ale, a bit on the sweet side, w/just enough hops to dry the palate

name: Houblon Chouffe
description: a unique marrying of the traditions of english ipas w/the innovations of american double ipas and the classic belgian way of brewing. a beautifully balanced tripel, hazy gold w/impres sive, long lasting head, big malty body, distinct hop dryness, expressive estery fruitiness

name: Kwak
description: brewed by bosteels, named for innkeeper pauwel kwak, who brewed this beer start - ing in 1791. a deep amber beer w/an earthy aroma; hearty & warming

name: Hommelbier
description: specialty of the van eecke family’s brewery in the small town of watou. a hoppy, golden-bronze top-fermented ale made from a blend of winter, summer & aromatic pale malts; soft water, from the brew ery’s own well; brewers’ gold & hallertau hops. roselike floweriness from the bottle-conditioning, orange-zestiness from the hops & a late, spicy, cumin-seed dryness. very refreshing & cleansing. try it before a meal

name: Gran Cru
description: flemish red ale. blend of 40% young sweet ale, 60% mature ale, aged in bordeaux casks for 2 years. not as sour as rodenbach, nor as sweet as duchesse

name: Ambrio
description: using only belgian hops, this mechelen brown-style ale is rich w/sweet caramel & raisin notes

name: Hopsinjoor
description: hoppy offering brewed w/goldings, spalt, haller tau & saaz. gently bitter, dry & subtle. not extreme, just delicious. a new favorite

name: Carolus D’Or
description: strong, deep copper-red color, complex aroma, warm finish

name: Cuvee Van De Keizer
description: brewed once a year on february 24, birthday of charles v. malty and brown with many layers of flavor

name: Cuvee Van De Keizer Blonde
description: yeasty aroma, boozy heat & fruity sweetness

name: Scaldis
description: known in belgium as "bush". a slow sipping ale. lots of upfront warmth & a malty bouquet

name: Lucifer
description: after bouncing around a bit, this brand has found a home at het anker. fruity and spicy, crisp and refreshing. not unlike duvel in style, and name

name: Duvel
description: a classic! this strong golden ale is surely one of the world’s most beautiful & elegant beers. prodigious creamy head, a champagne sparkle, notes of pear & a dry finish. fermented three times, bottle-conditioned and suitable for cellaring

name: Satan Gold
description: belgian strong ale, hazy gold w/white head; fruit-spicy-yeasty nose & palate w/grain & herbs coming in. some sweetness, possible minerality, in the finish

name: Satan Red
description: satan gold’s darker & maltier sibling

name: Special Block 6
description: very drinkable. moderately strong, reddishbrown ale. spritzy & light-bodied. food riendly

name: Samaranth Quadrium
description: sweetly malty & full-bodied quadrupel; complex flavors: dried fruit, marzipan & nuts

name: Hop-It
description: brewed as homage to american craft brewers w/european hops & pilsner malt. spicy, hoppy & delicious

name: Saissoniere
description: brewed at koningshoeven abbey. easy drinking farmhouse style ale w/notes of honey, lemon & cloves. great with food; low enough in alcohol for an extended session

name: XX Bitter
description: for a few hours each week on friday & saturday, the 100-year-old deca brewery in w. flanders is turned over to two friends, nino bacelle & guido devos, to make small batches of specialty brew. made w/haller & brewers gold hop varieties, xx is famous for its massive hoppiness

name: Kriek
description: beautiful, ruby-colored, dry & quite sour yet fairly easy to drink. sharp cherry upfront; earth, barnyard, wood notes in aroma & palate. slight sweetness comes only from the fresh whole tart cherries - no added sugar or syrup

name: Duchesse Du Bourgogne
description: refreshing flemish old red ale, matured in oak casks. smooth, rich texture w/interplay of passion fruit & chocolate, & a long dry, acidic finish

name: Vichtenaar (11.2oz)
description: flemish red-brown ale matured in oak casks for 8 months. fruity sour oak notes, flavors of madeira & vanilla, & the acidity of a fresh apple

name: Echt Kriekbier (11.2oz)
description: cherry ale based on vichtenaar w/ local sour cherries added during the maturation process in wood casks. final product is a blending of 1, 2 & 3-year old beers

name: Aged Pale Ale
description: 24-30 months in wood. old-golden-hued. oaky aroma w/hints of sherry & fruit, sourness in the finish

name: Oud Bruin
description: mahogany-colored; rich, soft, chocolatey notes, vanilla oakiness, dessert apple fruitiness, maybe passion fruit & restrained acidity. nice with duck

name: Toria
description: a bottle conditioned blond ale with a subtle, fruity palate and a pronounced hop character from a new brewery owned by a young family who are launching their brewery with this offering. delicious beginning

name: Toria Triple
description: bitter take on a triple style. hides it's strength with fresh hop flavor. 8.7% brewed w/ valerian & lemon balm

name: Tripel
description: creamy medium body, big alcohol

name: Brune
description: strong, malty brown, sweet

name: Rouge
description: kasteel brown ale matured 6 months w/sour cherries. good as an aperitif or dessert

name: Valeir Extra
description: belgian ipa. more easy drinking than american hop bombs. balanced & easy drinking. a bit of sweetness makes this a well-balanced brew

name: Divers
description: probably inspired by duvel, this strong blonde ale is from a long sleepy brewery, in business since 1818, recently become ambitious with its new brew master who married into his job. a spicy strong blonde ale that is spritzy and refreshing

name: Bière Brut
description: brewed & re-fermented in the bottle using the méthode champenoise. heady mix ture of phenolic alcohol & finely balanced by hops. long lingering hop finish w/fizziness on the tongue. tickles the nose like a sparkling wine

name: Dark Brut Reserve
description: brewed as the above-méthode champe - noise. strong & complex yet well-balanced. nose: citrus, barnyard, wood, horseblanket, malt, almonds, vanilla, powdery chocolate. spritzy yet creamy mouthfeel. notes of bitter dark chocolate, vanilla, wood, coffee, charcoal, leather, tobacco, nuts, spirits. velvety-smooth finish w/dark woody malt flavours. great w/chocolate. drinks easier than its abv suggests, so be careful
strong ale-full-bodied, gold-coloured w/ rich honey-like texture, & pleasant warming, slightly hoppy-dry lingering finish
deep dark ruby-brown quadrupel w/rich heavy aroma: malt, spices, caramel, raisins & dates; palate a bit lighter w/smooth texture & alcohol present. a sipper

name: Blonde Ale
description: brewer jose poncin is a chemist by day, a brewer by night, with a flair for the experimental. spicy, sparkling w/notes of fruit, butterscotch and eucalyptus

name: Singing Blonde
description: a rare brewpub beer from belgium that is available to us "across the pond". hidden strength. lots of yeast, a bit of honey like sweetness and sour funk. a window into the emerging brewpub scene in west flanders

name: Brut Des Flanders
description: the true champagne of bottled beers. extra ordinary sparkling ale is fermented in the bottle, followed by the traditional "remuage et dégorge ment" in the champagne region of france. fabulously aromatic, it tingles on the tongue w/carbo nation & has a fine dry finish

name: Piraat
description: hoppy interpretation of a strong golden ale w/lots of saaz character. gold-tobronze color, spicy hop aroma, creamy nutty palate, fruity dryness in the warming finish

name: Atomium Premier Gran Cru
description: 6 grains: barley, spelt, rye, corn, wheat & buckwheat. hazy orange, amber, flavored w/hops, coriander & orange zest

name: Gulden Draak (Golden Dragon)
description: the flagship of this famous brewery. dark brown triple ale w/a creamy head, natural malt, toffeelike sweetness w/hoppy accents. barleywine strength

name: Arabier
description: light and citrusy, pale and hoppy. a strong golden ale; sweetish w/hoppy aroma

name: Bos Keun
description: lightly spiced paasbier (blonde ale made for easter.) slightly sour with honey over - tones. pale and dry hopped

name: Oerbier
description: brown ale with a nice tartness and sweet finish. double dark and smooth with sweetness offset by licorice tones

name: Oerbier Reserva
description: specially reserved oerbier aged in bordeaux casks for 18 months. concentrated flavor & alcohol. rare & very limited

name: Stille Nacht
description: sour-spicy winter seasonal. claret-colored w/hints of apple in aroma & palate

name: Dulle Teve 10 Degrees
description: the website says: "dulle teve means mad bitch, but the us government does not like the name, so we said ‘tripel’." an all malt brew w/white candy in the kettle and refermented

name: Troublette
description: complex wallonian white ale made from 100% organically grown pilsner malt & raw wheat, w/styrian & saaz hops. perfumy, w/ very smooth palate & fruity acidity; dry finish

name: Saxo
description: wallonian blonde ale made w/munich & pilsner malt, raw wheat & saaz hops

name: Avec Les Bons Voeux
description: usually a holiday offering, but great anytime. rich & fruity w/a nice dry finish

name: Saison Du Pont
description: herbal, hoppy, peppery fruitiness; rocky head. long dry finish

name: Avril-Bière Du Table
description: a refreshing low-alcohol "table beer". great w/food or as a palate-cleansing starter before you follow w/stronger fare. good choice for when you want to have a few & need to be somewhere early the next morning. fills the niche and vastly superior to american ‘lite beers’. it’s dupont, so you know you won’t be disappointed

name: Foret
description: organic saison ale. belgium’s only certified organic ale. bold, dry and herbal. in gredients grown on their own farm

name: Moinette
description: true artisanal strong walloon ale. well-hopped; spice & ginger notes; fruity finish

name: Moinette Brun
description: creamy chestnut brown ale. nice, sweet malt flavor. new in the states

name: Biere Du Miel
description: in 1920, louis dupont, an engineer-agriculturist, was planning to emigrate to canada. to dissuade him, his father bought him the rimaux-deridder farm house brewery, renowned for its honey beer. 80 years later, louis’ heirs have revived the style. bottle-conditioned; delicately honey-scented balanced by a dry palate

name: Saison D’Erpe-Mere
description: very traditional hoppy saison w/ fruity-spicy elements; brewery founded in 2004

name: Jan De Lichte
description: "strong" double wit brewed with barley and wheat malts, oats and buckwheat. hazy gold, light effervescent body w/wheat & grass in nose. spicy, somewhat yeasty, softly malty, a little earthy. grass-citrus finish. easy-drinking and pleasant

name: Cuvée Angelique
description: made by the female members of opa aalst (local brand of zythos.) belgian doublestyle; rich dark fruit & spice. best beer yet from a new hopleaf favorite brewery

name: Saison
description: fruity, complex farmhouse ale. rustic, funky & refreshing.

name: Saison
description: nice spritz, notes of citrus & wheat, and a malty finish w/a a bit of tart wildness. subtle & delicious offering from one of the few female-run belgian breweries

name: Saison Rue
description: an unfiltered saison brewed with rye and brettanomyces. crisp with notes of citrus, pepper, floral hops and honey

name: Blonde Ale
description: refreshing, fruity, a bit of barnyard funk, subtle hops, yeast and fruit notes

name: Amber Ale
description: a slightly more malty version of the above beer. a bit fuller bodied

name: Red
description: full copper color, notably soft palate, hint of black current

name: White
description: firm dry body, slender for its gravity, w/plenty of hop charac ter in the finish & a quenching hint of acidity. a noble beer whose character is a bit different than the other chimays

name: Blue
description: characteristic chimay depth of aromatic fruitiness, a port among beers. the version in a corked 750ml bottle is called grand reserve. the larger bottle size and different method of sealing seem to mature the beer in a softer manner

name: La Trappe Quadruple
description: very strong full malt richness, brandy-like alcohol.

name: Isid’Or
description: an amber beer using the subtle and self-cultivated perle hops. caramel malt and a dry lingering finish. all profits go to their affiliated monasteries in uganda

name: Extra
description: huge copper-colored ale! licorice/dark chocolate, spicy aromas; full-bodied and richly malty. long and warming finish
copper, russet colored, earthy-sweet aroma and flavors; hints of caramel & raisins
tawny and fruity with a suggestion of figs
dark brown & rich with depths of fruity & chocolaty flavors.

name: Double
description: a dark brown ale, malty but quite dry

name: Triple
description: strong w/ a pale, almost pilsner color. its mash is made ‘exclusively of pilsner malts from germany & france, but following the classic procedure, candy sugar is added to the kettle. there are three hopping stages. faintly citrus fruitiness, rounded body, & alcoholic kick; this triple expresses its full character within 6 months of leaving the mona stery. strong herbal aroma and dense head

name: Orval
description: founded in 1070 by benedictines from calabria, and rebuilt many times over the centuries after being sacked in several conflicts. this beer, the only offering from this abbey, gains its unusual orangy color from the use of three malts plus white candy sugar in the kettle. dry-hopped secon dary fermentation, which lasts 5-7 weeks. bottle conditioning lasts for 2 months. this is a world classic

name: Tripel Imperiale
description: 2006 world beer championship platinum medal "superlative". very rich dark tripel.

name: Tripel
description: pale golden w/white fluffy head; effervescent; distinctive maltiness; fruity, spicy, yeasty.

name: Brune
description: ruby brown w/generous head; malty body, flavor fruity w/licorice & caramel notes , & a bt of hop bitterness

name: Saison
description: nice spritz, notes of citrus & wheat, and a malty finish w/a a bit of tart wildness. subtle & delicious offering from one of the few female-run belgian breweries

name: Witkap
description: banana & berry nose, lemony finish. lighter in body & alcohol than doubles & triples but w/the big aromatic profile typical of the style. quenchingly flavorful! what the monks drink for lunch

name: Pale
description: golden and perfumy; produced by dubocq of purnode in nanur province.

name: Brown
description: dark & chocolatey; made in bios in ertevelde, east flanders.

name: Blonde
description: fruit, yeast and malt w/light hop notes. one of the first belgians on our list

name: Brune Or Double
description: ripe and dried fruits, rich full body and creamy mouth feel.

name: Tripel Karmeliet
description: inspired by the 3-grain beer brewed in the 1600’s by the carmelites of dender monde; made by bosteels brewery in nearby buggenhout. launched in 1996 to acclaim. made from raw & malted barley, wheat & oats. golden to bronze w/a creamy head; great finesse & complexity. restrained hoppiness, generous spicing, fruity banana & vanilla character from the house yeast

name: Abt 12
description: richly textured brown ale so dark it’s almost ebony; smooth, creamy & full-bodied. very assertive, like a warming coconut brandy

name: Tripel
description: pale amber color w/a wonderful head, slightly sweet rose water aroma; orangey-grassy flavors of styrian hops in the finish

name: Prior 8
description: dark, sweet, mellow beer-essentially a dark tripel. ruby to purple color; smooth, creamy rich texture that‘s almost oily, malt-fruit complexity reminiscent of coconut

name: Pater 6
description: traditional dubbel, chestnut in color, very fruity w/notes of melon & very fresh banana, finishing w/slight bitterness. easy drinking

name: Blonde
description: a bit strong for a blonde. rocky head, floral aroma, subdued hoppiness, smooth mouthfeel

name: Dobbel
description: deep garnet dense meringue head w/chocolate notes, finishing dry & light. twice fermented, bottle-conditioned. from the oldest abbey in flanders

name: Tripel
description: the "burgundy of belgium" as abbey beers are called. twice world champion of the style! deep gold, spicy with a touch of apricots and vanilla

name: Dubbel 8
description: dark deep ruby w/decent head & lace. richly savory & sweet on the nose; big fruity & malty palate w/ chocolaty malts & toffeeish sweetness. yeast & dry wood, smoke & spicy alcohol in the finish. grows even better as it warms

name: Tripel 10
description: hazy gold-peach amber w/massive head & good lacing. light aromas of malt, alcohol, bread yeast & fruit. flavors sweet, toasty, w/caramel, dark malt, some fruit. medium full body, generous carbonation, tongue-coating, alcohol warmth in the finish

name: Maredsous Blonde 6
description: brewed since 1963 by duvel moortgat for the monks of the abbey near namur. this is the lightest & most easy-drinking of the three. fruity, spicy, w/mildly dry finish

name: Gueuze
description: a classic gueuze blend of 1-, 2- and 3- year-old lambics, fermented a second time in the bottle. unsweetened, unfiltered, best served at cellar temperature

name: Kriek
description: gueuze fermented w/local schaerbeek cherries only, macerated for 5-6 months allowing them to dissolve completely

name: Rosé De Gambrinus
description: gueuze fermented with whole raspberries; cherry accent

name: Bruocsella 1900 Gran Cru
description: for afficionados. unblended old lambic chosen by the master brewer. smooth; nearly still. the "single malt" of lambic. aged in oak at least 3 years

name: Gueuze
description: neither filtered nor centrifuged. quite traditional & cidery. very complex palate with lots of aromatic flavors, including sour apple & lemon juice

name: Gueuze Fond Tradition
description: very tart & authentic classic gueuze-30% wheat, 70% barley-spontaneously fermented, oak-aged to perfection

name: Oude Gueuze
description: lambic from the last free-standing blender (negociant) in the world, each bottle aged over three years. "refreshingly fruity and rhubarby flavor," says michael jackson

name: Oude Kriek
description: similar to the oude gueuze, brewed w/cherries.

name: Oudbeitje
description: strawberries in the nose & palate! 2-year-old lambic (blend of boon and girardin) conditioned with 150kg of natural straw berries per 600-liter barrel. tart and dry; a fine aperitif

name: Experimental Cassis
description: one-off batch black current lambic from sidy hanssens, daughter of jean, who saved the tradition of a non-brewing blender of lambic. beautiful tart fruit

name: Experimental Raspberry
description: one-off batch black current lambic from sidy hanssens, daughter of jean, who saved the tradition of a non-brewing blender of lambic. beautiful tart fruit

name: Oud Beersel Gueuze
description: following spontaneous fermentation in wooden barrels (no yeast or sugar added), young and old lambic are blended. tart, refreshing, naturally sour w/musty sweetness. "the white sparkling wine of the beer world

name: Oud Beersel Kriek
description: whole fresh cherries added to gueuze.the acidity of champagne; bouquet & delicate flavor of cherries; balance of almondy drynes

name: Oud Beersel Framboise
description: whole fresh raspberries added to young lambic, providing seasoning and sparking another fermentation, resulting in a product of great complexity. as with the kriek, this exhibits the acidity of champagne, the bouquet and delicate flavor of raspberries, and a balance of almondy dryness

name: Oude Gueuze
description: unsweetened blend of 1, 2 & 3 -year-old lambics. tart with palate-quenching hop finish. very rare

name: Kriek
description: pure fruit & unflinching sourness. militantly traditional & uncompromising. a superb example of belgian brewing art

name: Cassis
description: tart and sweet, tasting of currants.

name: Pomme
description: tart apple aroma & flavor w/slight lambic sourness in the background.

name: Framboise
description: magnificent aroma, delicate raspberry palate w/undertones of fruity acidity; elegant, sparkling clean natural taste, lovely rose color

name: Peche
description: sparkling, refreshing taste of peaches. flavorful and beautifully balanced. wonder ful in place of cider or champagne

name: Kriek
description: beautiful pour: deep red w/pink head, & lovely lacing as you drink. big cherry nose w/a bit of yeast. rich thick smooth mouthfeel, slight tartness & plenty of cherry flavor, sweetness till the end

name: Cuvee Rene Gueuze
description: unfiltered & aged-in-bottle "gran cru". named for brewery founder rene lindeman. cidery, winey palate; complex flavor

name: Faro
description: in traditional cafes, gueuze lambic was often served with a sugar bowl so that patrons could adjust the tartness the way coffee drinkers adjust the bitterness to their taste with sugar. faro is a gueuze that is finished at the brewery with a bit of confectioners sugar to tone down the tartness for you

name: Kriek
description: not exactly cherry lambic, but made from spontaneously-fermented brown ale

name: Framboise
description: raspberry

name: Mirabelle
description: plum

name: Fraises
description: strawberry

name: Dubbel Reserve
description: dark walnut color, toasted caramel & chocolate notes. rich, creamy mouthfeel, near wine-like nature

name: Four Ale
description: brewed with 4 malts, 4 hop varieties, & 4 sugars (light candy, dark candy, light golden molasses, & date sugar) & fermented 4 times, each with a different strain of belgian yeast

name: Fluxus
description: first beer brewed in rob todd’s new brewery. 25% rye malt & flavored with yarrow; hopped w/warrior & brewers gold. herbal character

name: Tripel Reserve
description: lighter in color than the double. complex fruit & spice aroma complemented by a full palate with suggestions of honey. long warm finish

name: Black
description: rob todd’s first stout is a roasty, toasted malt & chocolate brew made with german 2-row barley, torrified wheat, & oats refer - mented in bottle w/belgian yeast. typically allagash & awesome

name: Victor Ale
description: another rob todd experiment: beer plus 100 lbs of red chancellor grapes

name: Pere Jacques
description: inspired by his many journeys to belgium, brewer greg hall presents to chicago his homage to trappist rochfort

name: Matilda
description: brewer greg hall’s homage to orval trappist ale includes a rare yeast that imparts a fruity spiciness. lots of hops balances the complex maltiness. enjoy w/mussels

name: Sofie
description: farmhouse, saison. effervescent, hazy golden color w/notes of orange citrus, herbs & flowers and a bit of wild yeast funkiness. dry finish

name: Juliet
description: fermented w/wild yeasts & aged in cabernet barrels for 6 months with blackberries. tart, fruity and a bit sour. wine like tannins and woodiness

name: Bourbon County Stout
description: outstanding stout aged 100 days in bourbon casks, from the pioneer in the process. huge roasted coffee, chocolate & vanilla flavors w/bourbon aroma & heat. rare, expensive & worth it. 2008 vintage

name: Fleur
description: a belgian style pale ale brewed with super styrian, styrian goldings and saaz hops and hibiscus flowers and kobucha tea

name: Inferno Ale
description: belgian strong pale ale. fruit yeast & spice. an american delirium tremens

name: Devotion Ale
description: belgian pale ale fermented w/3 yeasts, northern brewer tettnang hops. effervescent w/ notes of orange, apricots & honey

name: Lost & Found
description: dark belgian double style brewed with raison puree. great yeast, caramel malt, subtle hops and dark fruit. deliciously complex

name: Judgment Day
description: strong quadruple-style, hopped w/ challenger & east kent goldings. brewed with raisins; rich

name: Avant Guard
description: bready aroma & taste. floral hoppiness, yeast & citrus w/a good deal of spritz

name: Angel’s Share 2009
description: aged for 12 months in heaven hill bour - bon casks. vanilla, dark fruit, toffee and alcohol heat. rare and special. limited availability. ask your server

name: Golden Monkey
description: authentic triple-style w/german malts & belgian yeast, w/ fruit & floral notes some spice & sweetness

name: Ommegang
description: top-fermented & bottle-conditioned for a fruity, aromatic burgundian brew

name: Hennepen Ale
description: farmhouse-style ale. robust hoppy saison style w/crisp finish

name: Rare Voss
description: brabant-style ale. copper-colored, spicy, light on the tongue, elusive fruitiness, nutty finish

name: Biere De Mars
description: hazy amber french style ale. a bit of brettanomyces funk, malty sweetness and a dry hoppy finish

name: 3 Philosophers
description: noel blake’s winning concept in the real beer contest to "describe your ideal beer": a blend of lindeman’s kriek & ommegang ale. fruity, spicy & strong

name: Chocolate Indulgence Stout
description: belgian chocolate & chocolate malt combine for a rich, subtle tryly unique stout. perle hops cap the finish. limited availability. ask your server.

name: Ommegeddon
description: a dose of funky brettanomyces yeast takes this towards the wild side. a bit sour. refrshing w/dry finish

name: Zuur
description: collaboration with fellow duvel, moortgat brewery leifman’s. a blend of oud bruin and a separate batch of oud bruin aged w/cherries. the blend is then again blended with goudenband. mildly tart, a bit funky w/woodiness & fruit notes

name: Local 1
description: strong golden ale. naturally carbonated, 100% bottle refermentation. german malts & hops, mauritius demerara cane sugar, belgian yeast. somewhat spicy, fruity, finishing dryer. first beer packaged using the brewery’s new brooklyn bottling line & warm room

name: Local 2
description: dark ale brewed w/belgian dark candy sugar & ny state wildflower honey

name: Black Chocolate Stout
description: russian imperial stout brewed w/a blend of specialty malts, mashed 3 times & hopped willamette & american fuggle

name: Brooklyn Black Ops
description: russian imperial stout aged 4 months in bourbon casks, bottled flat and refermented with champagne yeast. limited availability. only 940 cases produced

name: Maudite
description: mahogany-colored, rich & complex.

name: Blanche De Chambly
description: produced from a blend of quebec unmalted wheat and a very pale barley malt to which spices & natural aromatics are added along with a light hopping

name: Chambly Noire
description: smooth & creamy, dark & malty, easy drinking

name: Éphémère
description: a light wheat ale brewed with apples and spices. refreshing & aromatic

name: Fin Du Monde
description: triple fermented in the style of belgian trappist triples. slightly tart w/balanced flavors of wild spices, malt and hops

name: La Terrible
description: dark abbey ale, strong and full of roasted malt flavor with a fruity aroma

name: Trois Pistoles
description: mellow flavor, dark color w/a ripe fruit aroma reminiscent of old port

name: Quatre-Centième ("400")
description: dubbel style brewed for the 400th anniversary of quebec city, w/4 different spices, herbs repre senting each century. lightbodied, slightly tart, sour

name: Quelque Chose
description: featuring dark malts & wild cherries (soaked in slightly bitter ale for months before their addition), q.c. is brewed to be served hot in winter & cold in summer. great w/strong cheeses, with or as dessert, or on the rocks as an aperitif. yum

name: Don De Dieu
description: brewed once a year, in dec. triple-style, bottle-fermented abbey-type beer. made w/unmalted wheat; cloudy w/suspended yeast; the color of a white beer w/golden highlights. strong yet mellow

name: PranQster
description: belgian-style golden ale. floral nose, full fruity flavor & a clean finish

name: Le Merle
description: rustic flanders-style "saison" ale. mildly sour with nice hops in background, highly carbonated & refreshing, clearly inspried by dupont & well done

name: Brother Thelonious
description: dark brown belgian strong ale. dark fruits, spices, caramel, brown sugar, figure in both nose & palate. rich & mouthfilling; yeasty sweetness & alcohol; also some hop bitterness. inspired by thelonious monk & released in conjunction w/the thelonious monk institute of jazz (brewery contributes to the institute to support jazz education)

name: Oro De Calabaza
description: brewed in the french bière de garde tradition. lush & spicy, gently hoppy

name: Calabaza Blanca
description: white ale w/orange peel & coriander. tart with a dry finish

name: Whaleback White
description: fermented with wild yeasts and aged in french oak, this is set apart from all other belgian white ales. it has the lemon and orange notes common to the style but is a bit bit more wild and bit more spritzy. very refreshing

name: Good Harbor Golden
description: biere de garde style beer. tart, dry, with completely hidden alcohol notes. complex and refreshing. a personal favorite

name: Fat Tire Amber Ale
description: toasty, biscuity maltiness so pleasantly balanced w/crisp hoppiness
brussels-style black ale based on a 16th century recipe brewed w/lager yeast at a warm temperatures for an easy-drinking full malt flavor

name: Trans Atlantic Kriek
description: brewed & aged in casks at boon in belgium. after cherries are added it’s shipped refrigerated to new belgium where it is blended with a golden lager. an american-belgian creation

name: La Folie
description: brewmaster peter bouckaert came to new belgium from rodenbach and this beer reflects that legacy. aged in french oak casks, it has the vinous sour flavor one would expect. complex and delicious. 6% lbs. of red chancellor grapes

name: Reverend
description: belgian-style quadrupel ale. tawny-colored with hints of dark cherries, currents & molasses

name: Salvation
description: belgian-style strong golden ale. cham pagne-like w/apricot & peach aromas

name: Pale Ale
description: blond-colored, firm-bodied pale ale made from a balanced blend of pale & biscuit malts. spicy floral hop aroma & flavor

name: 3rd Coast Beer
description: golden easy drinker. crisp & refreshing; bitter finish.

name: 3rd Coast Old Ale
description: strong barleywine style. deep amber-colored w/ vintage brandy-like character

name: Expedition Stout
description: american take on imperial stout. massive & rich. a sipper.

name: Porter
description: dark ale for all occasions. blend of dark malts imparting flavors of coffee & chocolate w/some smoky roasted notes

name: Cherry Stout
description: roasty malt & tart michigan cherries. when available

name: Kalamazoo Stout
description: deep dark, full-bodied roasty stout.

name: Amber
description: bell’s’ flagship beer, deep copper-colored & richly flavored. mostly pale malts, but also some munich & caramel malts, bring a slightly sweet flavor that is balanced by a melange of american hops

name: Two-Hearted Ale
description: bell’s most bitter ale, beautifully copper colored, w/dense creamy head & full blast of hops

name: St. Ambrose Oatmeal Stout
description: draft favorite in the early days of hopleaf, now back in chicago in bottles only. lots of great flavor-especially roasty coffee, bitter chocolate & hops-in a relatively

name: ESB
description: this everyday drinker has lingering bitterness & some citrus notes. light body & moderate alcohol make it a session ale. one of the pioneering craft breweries to offer beer in cans

name: French Country Ale
description: "domaine dupage". easy drinking caramel malty ale inspired by the biere de garde style of n. france, brewed nearby

name: Hopfen-Weisse
description: collaboration between garrett oliver and hans peter drexler, the malted wheat sweetness is tamed by dryhopping with american hops. lots of citrus notes

name: Genesis Ale
description: crisp, smooth, balanced between a west coast pale and amber ale, easy enough to be a session ale. supple malt sweetness, pronounced hops

name: Messiah Bold
description: deep brown session ale made w/rich dark malts, complex but mild hops, some nutty & sweet notes, decent carbonation

name: Origin Ale
description: imperial amber brewed w/5 barley malts, wheat, 6 nw hops varieties & the juice of pomegranates; inspired by deut

name: Bitterweet Lenny’s Ripa
description: rye-based double ipa tribute to lenny bruce-"brewed w/an obscene amount of malt & hops." tons of big flavor

name: Burning River Pale Ale
description: named after the infamous 1969 combustion of the cuyahoga river. firm-bodied for its style. asser tively hoppy, balanced by subtle malt flavors

name: Edmund Fitzgerald Porter
description: roasty aroma, bittersweet, coffee flavors, bold hop presence

name: The Eliot Ness
description: deep amber-red w/fragrant malt aroma. rich caramelized malt and noble hop flavors; crisp clean finish. 5.8% moderate alcohol package

name: Raison D’Etre
description: deep mahogany ale brewed w/beet sugar, green raisins and belgian yeast, "complexas a fine red wine." malt advocate magazine’s american beer of the year, 1999

name: Raison D’Extra
description: huge version of rasion d’etre, brewed w/brown sugar & raisins. taste of figs & molasses. alcohol heat

name: World Wide Stout
description: variable availability. please ask your server. very dark, rich, roasty, complex, huge; brewed w/a ridiculous amount of barley. thick but lively mouthfeel, strong, sweet notes. have one with (or as) dessert

name: 60 Minute IPA
description: a session india pale brewed w/warrior, amarillo & "mystery hop x". powerful w/ lots of citrusy hop character & notes of cedar, pine, floral & candied orange

name: 90 Minute IPA
description: this imperial ipa features a single constant 90-minute hop addition-cascade, columbus & chinook-balanced by plenty of english 2-row barley, then dry hopped to reach 90 ibu. the 2003 cham pion of realbeer.com’s battle of the beers

name: 120 Minute IPA
description: variable availability. please ask your server. 120 ibu monster of an ipa. extremely alcoholic. dry-hopped for a month after a 2-hour boil with hops. aged for another month w/whole hops. hops hops and more hops

name: Fort
description: one ton of raspberries per batch. 2-month fermentation. very complex, very strong. this one’s to share and then take a cab home

name: Palo Santo Marron
description: "holy brown tree". american brown ale aged on this super-dense paraguayan wood, which im parts its unique caramelvanilla-chocolate profile. roasty, woody, really like nothing else

name: Midas Touch
description: handcrafted ancient ale: a beverage based on residue found in the drinking vessels of king midas’ tomb (yes, he really existed, though the golden touch is just a story.) made w/white muscat grapes, honey & saffron. smooth & dry

name: Burton Baton
description: blend of oak-aged english strong ale dfh’s 90-minute ipa. citrus notes from north western hops meld w/the oak’s vanilla notes

name: Squall
description: first generation bottling of a future addition to the dogfish collection of beers! bottle-conditioned imperial ipa. dry-hopped with 6 hop varieties and unfiltered

name: Pride And Joy
description: the floyds’ take on a british mild or bitter style. more assertive in strength with nice hop character. only 29 ibu but the hop quality really comes through. great everyday drinker

name: Gumballhead
description: summer seasonal wheat beer with an unusually aggressive amarillo hop punch. refreshing and bitter

name: Hopdevil Ale
description: rich german malts & whole-flower american hops. very well-balanced, nice bitter finish

name: Wild Devil Ale
description: hop devil re fermented with a wild yeast. very limited

name: Golden Monkey
description: authentic triple-style w/german malts & belgian yeast, w/ fruit & floral notes some spice & sweetness.

name: Devil Dancer
description: occasional availability. ask your server. massive dark mahogany double ipa with huge malt character balanced by its big 112 ibus. flavors of grapefruit & pine & flowers also present. dry-hopped for 26 days straight w/a combination of 10 hop varieties. powerful, delicious

name: Dirty Bastard Scotch Ale
description: reddish brown in color. malty & sweet, typical of the style but a bit hoppier than most scotch ales. for its strength, quite a smooth drink

name: Red’s Rye
description: rich & hoppy. brewed with rye and 4 belgian caramel malts.

name: Breakfast Stout
description: flaked oats, bitter & sweet chocolate and sumatra & kona coffee. this creamy beer has the ingredients for a fine breakfast to be enjoyed all day long. seasonal availability. ask your server

name: Kentucky Breakfast
description: occasional availability. ask your server. an 11.2% bourbon-cask-aged version of the breakfast stout

name: Dragon’s Milk
description: american strong ale aged in oak barrels. soft, rich caramel-malt character w/deep vanilla tones & dark fruit notes

name: Crooked Tree IPA
description: made by simply doubling all of the ingredients, except the water, of their crooked tree ipa. bitter & citric, huge in every way. great lingering finish

name: Porter
description: rich, dark & complex, though slightly lighter in body than many porters. caramel, chocolate, deep coffee notes. america’s first porter

name: Old Foghorn
description: deep caramel color, rich hoppy nose, malty taste. hints of fruit, especially plum, offset by the rousing hop character.

name: Liberty Ale
description: heavily hopped (cascade) w/copper color & hoppy nose, creamy persistent head. first brewed in 1975 to commemorate paul revere’s ride!

name: Small Beer
description: revives an ancient tradition of brewing two distinct beers from one mash. made from sparging a second time the same mash that produces old foghorn. like a modern bitter

name: Steam
description: a true original, steam beer lies some where between ale & lager. unique combination of flavors, well-hopped w/a pleasantly malty character

name: Pale Ale
description: since 1981, an american classic.

name: Bigfoot
description: 25th release of sierra’s classic barleywine. dense, complex & malty w/plenty of chinook, cascade & centenniel hops for balance.

name: Torpedo Ale
description: extra ipa bittered w/magnum, finished w/ magnum & crystal, dry-hopped w/magnum, crystal & the new citra hops. a delicious hopfest!

name: Kellerweis
description: only american hefeweizen using traditional bavarian open fermentation method. plenty of tasty yeast & banana esters. this is the best american hefeweizen we’ve had; puts many of the german ones to task

name: Wipeout IPA
description: classic west coast ipa, hopped w/ amarillo, centenniel & simcoe varieties. a bit of caramel hop for balance, but it’s the hops that rule here

name: Old 38 Stout
description: named for a retired steam engine on the fort bragg-willits "skunk" run through the california red woods. onyx-dark, smooth, firm-bodied stout; toasted character, coffee notes of dark malts & roasted barley

name: Old Rasputin Imperial Stout
description: a style from england favored by the russian imperial court. huge, malty & well-hopped. this beer, like rasputin, stands up to anything & will not die

name: XII Anniversary Old Rasputin
description: a bourbon-barrel-aged version of the classic russian imperial stout. drink while it lasts. very limited.

name: Old Stock Ale
description: perhaps the classic american old ale, eminently cellarable. made w/imported british malt & hops. rich mahogany color, wonderful "evening ender."

name: Scrimshaw Pilsner
description: european-style pils brewed with munich & klages malts and hallertauer & tettnang hops. mildly hoppy w/a dry finish

name: Red Seal Ale
description: copper-red pale ale with wonderful hop, malt balance

name: Ruination Ale
description: 100 ibu hop monster brewed w/truckloads of columbus & centennial hops. nothing subtle here. you like bitter? drink this

name: Levitation Ale
description: want a low-alcohol full-flavor, nicely hopped amber, red ale? this is it! great for a long session at 4.4% but delivers plenty of taste

name: Arrogant Bastard
description: despite its name, this beer is quite balanced and agreeable. not too strong, too hoppy or to malty, just delicious

name: Sublimely Self Righteous
description: lots of roasted malt with some grapefruit & pine notes. a bit on the strong side with a bitter finish that covers up the heat

name: Farson’s Lacto Stout
description: from the makers of our namesake hopleaf pale ale! brewed according to the original 1946 recipe w/unfermentable lactose adding sweetness & body, this black beer sports a pale brown head, red licorice aromas, moderate maltiness, some chocolate & herbal notes. sweet w/pleasant dryness in the finish. this style, aka milk stout, was originally made w/whey, was high in b vitamins and low in alcohol, and so was rationed to pregnant & nursing mothers during wwii

name: Palanfrina
description: made w/ malted barley & local roasted chestnuts. hazy brown & medium-bodied.

name: Malthus Birolla
description: brewed w/roasted chestnuts & honey from thorn trees, all local to the beautiful northern italy mountain lake country. refermented w/more honey, hopped w/ kent goldings & cascades. worth the money

name: Rubis-Lamponi
description: sour raspberry ale from the lazio region.

name: Super Baladin
description: a surprise from italy! originating from a 9th-century recipe, similar to a belgian triple. an english yeast strain is used for primary fermentation. warm apricot, flowers, bananas & bitter almonds aromas. such flavors plus citrus & warm malt come through strongly

name: Al-Iksir
description: called a demi-sec ale, its primary fermentation uses islay scotch whiskey yeast. lively carbonization, flavors of baking spices, dark fruits and biscuits

name: Nora
description: inspired by the beers of ancient egypt. spiced with ginger, myrrh, & orange peel.

name: Panil Barriquée
description: triple-fermented, first in stainless steel, then in cognac casks & finally in the bottle. sour red ale, unfiltered, unpasteurized & with no added sugars, it revives the lamentably fading flemish & dutch sour reds, oud bruin styles

name: Cassissona
description: sparkling cassis beer from tiny birrificio italiano. munich, pilsner & caramel malts. small amount of cassis added at beginning of fermentation, matured for 6 mo's. rich, fruity aromas. vanilla & dry hoppy finish. beautiful, unique bottle

name: Dolii Raptor
description: this is their sought after demon hunter ale aged in barbera wine casks for 6 months. dark brown color, notes of tart cherries, oak, & vanilla. expensive, yes but worth it

name: Draco
description: brewed w/6 malts, fermented 3 times. fresh blueberries, yeast & malt sugar are added during the second. great aromatics

name: Quarta Runa
description: oven-baked fresh peaches are added during fermentation to this malted barley & wheat brew. peach flavor is subtle, in the background.

name: Gran Reserva
description: brown ale made with 12 different malts, aged in barbera wine casks. lightly carbonated, vinous with notes of tobacco, oak and raisins.

name: Bran Reserva
description: strong brown ale aged in barbera wine barrels. 12 different malts. including pilsner, vienna, pale, dark, caramel, chocolate, black, wheat.

name: Blonde Palanfrina
description: an old-school pilsner. unlike nearly all modern pilsners, it is open-fermented, unfiltered and unpasteurized. saaz hops used in moderation. a bit of citrus and malty sweetness. a different take on a common style

name: Aventinus
description: the world’s oldest top-fermenting wheat doppel-bock, made since 1907 as a creative response to bottom-fermented dop pel bocks popular at the time. 8% "aventinus has a huge head, an insistent sparkle, malty notes in the nose, chocolate, fruit & spices in the palate and slightly clove-like finish

name: 1809 Berliner Weisse
description: one of the rare, antique & interesting regional beer styles of germany. a wheat beer brewed with top-fermenting yeast & lactobacillus culture w/wort that is not boiled but heated to just below boiling before transfer to open fermenters. germans are forbidden by reinhetsgebot (the pure beer law of 1516) to add anything but water, grain, hops & yeast to beer, but they often subvert the law when serving berlingerweisse by offering it "rot oder grun"-red on green-by adding raspberry or woodruff syrup. at hopleaf you may have it pure, red or green. tart, sour & acidic, a historic adventure in beer

name: Schwarzbier
description: brewed by kulmbacher, this classic black beer is called "the black pils" it’s unusually dry for a dark lager.

name: Rauchbier
description: a smoked beer whose flavor comes from the beechwood fire underneath the malt drying kiln; smoke penetrates the malt. dark, aromatic bottom-fermented beer. cellar-matured

name: Gose
description: top-fermented wheat beer, 60% wheat, 40% barley, plus coriander, salt & lactic acid bacteria. a rare german beer that’s not "reinheitsgebot"-it has ingredients other than malt, hops, yeast & water. refreshing & full of interesting flavor

name: Pils
description: typifies the very dry style of pils made in germa ny’s far north. emphatic hop aroma, a dry start and a long bitter finish

name: Ur Pils
description: pale golden, light, dry and balanced.

name: Munster Alt
description: in the land of lagers, alt is the rare german ale. pale gold w/herbaceous aroma & dry finish

name: Alt
description: the classic duesseldorfer altbier: mediumbodied w/balanced, clean maltiness; hops & dryness in the finish. michael jackson calls this "the most assertive, complex and characterful of the alts."

name: Non-Alcoholic
description: the only non-alcoholic beer that adheres to the german pure beer law of 1516.

name: Samichlaus
description: once "the world’s strongest beer". made in switzerland for over 20 yrs. brewed only on st. nicholas day (dec. 6th) then lagered for 10 months before bottling for the next year’s celebration. 4 malts: 1 pale, 3 dark. fermented at high temps for 2 wks., it exhibits densely malty creaminess w/some yeast notes, & a warming brandy-like alcohol finish. great w/robust dishes, chocolate, or on its own after dinner

name: Samichlaus Helles
description: strong and sippable! sweet & alcoholic aroma; pours bright gold w/no head. clinging honey sweetness to start, followed by alcoholic heat, yeast & malt, faint cherry? despite uncarbonated appearance, it sparkles on the tongue

name: Trumer Pils
description: traditional european craft pilsner recipe from the 400-year old trumer brewery in salzburg, purchased by hops merchant joseph sigl in 1776, held by the sigl family ever since (today run by josef sigl vii.) because this style travels so poorly, to provide a fresh product to the us, the sigls built a second brewery in berkeley, cal., which has exceptionally soft water nearly identical to salzburg’s. the beer: delicate spicy nose w/citrus accent, balanced smoothness. crisp, clean, well-rounded w/a very soft bitter finish back of palate. much milder hops profile than often found in the style

name: La Bavaisienne
description: bière de garde, lightly hopped, w/rich amber color, dense head, malty aroma & rich, sweet flavor

name: L’Amaltheé
description: brewed by a transplanted belgian goat cheese farmer in a tiny village in far south-western france. he grows his own barley & malts & feeds the spent grains to his goats. an orgainc original that harkens back to another age of farmhouse brewing. unfiltered & cellar-aged for 2 years

name: 3 Monts
description: great bière de garde from n. france. fresh light aroma; strong, spicy & slightly hoppy palate

name: Gavroche
description: french amber, red ale, light-bodied for a beer that packs a bit of a punch. nice spice, hop character, & spritz. easy drinking

name: Pur Malt
description: top-fermented all-malt, filtered ale. very strong, golden ale; smooth, almost fluffy, starting candyish w/peppery alcohol flavors, finishing surprisingly dry

name: Old Brewery Pale Ale
description: a light "session" ale, known as "old brewery bitter" in the u.k.

name: Oatmeal Stout
description: on early labels, described as nutritional & recommended for lactating mothers, this bittersweet ale is hearty & substantial

name: Nut Brown Ale
description: walnut-colored w/a nutty, roasty palate

name: Imperial Stout
description: brewed to a high alcohol level to survive transport to the czarist courts in st. peters-burg, this is a rich, roasty ale w/alcohol warmth & flavor

name: Bitter
description: master brewer peter scholey of the late lamented brakspear brewery is brewing classic english ales including this easy-drinking, low-alcohol session ale. challenger & boadica hops & maris otter malt in perfect balance

name: Porter
description: several bottles of porter recovered from an 1825 english channel shipwreck found their way to brewing scientist keith thomas in 1988. one bottle yielded enough yeasty sediment to culture up & use in a whitbread porter recipe from the period. once the most popular brewing style in england, it fell out of favor & for a time was not produced at all. in a great revival, the style is presented here in its original glory

name: Porter
description: 7 malts, fuggle hops. roast coffee, chocolate & toasted malt flavors. brewed in greenwich, home of time itself

name: Abbaye De St. Bon-Chien
description: delightfully complex belgian-style strong ale from brasserie des franches-montagnes in the jura mtns., nw border region of switzerland. treads the boundary between port, wine & beer-aged in wooden casks previously used to age merlot, merlot cabernet, whisky and then grappa; then finally blended from different casks for optimal balance & complexity. amazing nose featuring spices (cinnamon, wood), fruit, spirits, licoricey, vegetal dry ness. palate features grapes, chocolate, vanilla, brown sugar! smooth & velvety, turning slightly vinous w/very subdued bitterness. long port-like finish. great with rich foods like duck, balsamic vinegar or very dark chocolate. only 1,000 bottles released for us market in 2006. named in fond memory of the late brewery cat

name: Pub Draft
description: available in 120 countries in 19 variations of which only 6 come from the original st. james gate brewery in dublin, including this one, the nitrogen-capsuled can. the brewery claims to use the original yeast; all the grain for the st. james version is grown in ireland

name: Green Line
description: only within chicago city limits & only as draft. local malted barley & all american hops; environmentally friendly, economical, very tasty. wonderful malty backbone w/just the right amt. of hops for refreshing finish. true everyday drinker

name: Pere Jacques
description: brewer greg hall’s homage to trappist rochfort. strong, dark, & sweet belgian-style ale w/banana & stone fruit notes

name: Pepe Nero
description: mahogany-colored farmhouuse ale, brewed w/ black peppercorns, 4 malts (pilsner, rye, crystal rye, black) and pilgrim & saaz hops

name: Maudite
description: mahogany-colored, rich-tasting & complex

name: White
description: traditional belgian-style wheat beer, light & slightly cloudy w/a blend of spices

name: Big Little Beer
description: collaboration w/beer advocate’s allstrom bros., a lighter "second mash" small beer made from the grain used to brew little big beer, a barleywine fermented w/a trappist ale yeast. light, crisp & bready

name: Hoss Rye Lager
description: based on the marzen lagers of germany. rich, layered malt notes; hints of cherry & dark fruits dominate; slightly earthy, spicy character from the rye. crisp & dry finish

name: Resistance IPA
description: 4 weeks minimum aging in oak foudres, this beer brings everything we like about hops up front but balances them w/malt, & time in wood. a subtle & distinctive ipa in a sea of headbangers

name: Dynamo Copper Lager
description: our neighborhood brewery, just 0.42 mile west of hopleaf. drink local! drink fresh! vienna & munich malts, perle & hallertau hops brew up a smooth, crisp, thirst-quenching easy drinker

name: Raison D’Etre
description: deep mahogany ale brewed with beet sugar, green raisins and belgian yeast, "complex as a fine red wine. malt advocate magazine’s american beer of the year, 1999

name: Wee Geech Pale Ale
description: brewed for san francisco beer week, which started feb.11, a few barrels snuck into chicago. in the midst of the strong beer season, here’s one of full flavor, yet moderate in alcohol. plenty of hops in the finish

name: Two-Hearted Ale
description: longtime hopleaf favorite. bell’s most bitter ale, beautifully copper colored, w/dense creamy head & full blast of hops

name: Prima Pils
description: german pilsner malt and czech & german hops. classic european pilsner, made in usa

name: Alpha King Ale
description: robust malt flavor & medium body, balanced by strong dry-hopping. deep orange color, bold citrus hop aroma & a dry finish

name: Racer 5
description: full-bodied american pale ale with generous amounts centennial, chinook, cascade & columbus hops

name: Pale Ale
description: from a brewery better known here for beer at the extremes, a balanced, easy-drinking & traditional british style pale ale. nice malt, subtle hops (magnum & ahtanum) make this foodfriendly & a nice session ale

name: Double Bastard (Imperial)
description: malty sweetness, molasses, caramel, vanilla, & hop bitterness combine to bury the alcohol heat

name: St. Ambroise Oatmeal Stout
description: once an all-the-time hopleaf draft pick is back after a decade’s absence. coffee & roasted malt aroma. bitter hops & chocolate flavor

name: Daisy Cutter Pale Ale
description: aromatic amer. pale all the way from lincoln ave. hops are huge on the nose & linger in the finish

name: Steam
description: a true original, steam beer lies somewhere between ale & lager. unique combination of flavors, well-hopped w/a pleasantly malty character

name: Glissade
description: sn’s not known for lagers, but this spring pale bock (it’s already spring in cali.) is a great example of getting the subtle things right. all the things we like about fresh draft lager at a beer hall in germany-lost in the old bottles & kegs imported into the states-are here to smell & taste. very balanced yeast, sweet malt, hops character. alcohol in check, this is an easy drinker

name: Porter
description: medium body, easy-drinking with lots of roasted malt, coffee, dark chocolate and hop flavor. in chicago, a hopleaf draft exclusive

name: Dortmunder Gold
description: smooth lager w/more body & less hops than a pilsner, less malt & more hops than a munich style lager. a great "session beer"

the best thing about autumn and winter at hopleaf is the annual return of st b 12 on draft! notes of dark fruit, biscuits and yeast. hidden strong alcohol. complex & warming and the closest we get to westvleteren 12 same recipe, town and water source

name: Avec Les Bon Voeux
description: the strongest of dupont’s farmhouse ale offerings, but the alcohol isn’t all that detectable. a touch of honey sweetness, grassiness, a bit of hop bitterness, some of the distinctive dupont yeasty funk & a nearly perfect amount of spritz. a perfect beer

name: Hop Ruiter
description: brewed for american importer v&dw by scheld-brouwerij to revive the full hop & yeasty funk flavor being lost in many mass-produced belgian golden ales in their producers’ efforts to please a wider audience. here is a return to the old school

name: Winter Bock
description: a huge winter favorite at hopleaf. chestnut coored ale brewed w/ honey, very easy-drinking w/some kick to fortify you against the chill

name: Belgoo Magus
description: brewed w/barley malt, wheat malt, oats, german wheat (triticum spelta) & saaz hops

name: Delirium Tremens
description: strong blonde ale w/excellent sweet, dry balance. very rewarding

name: Kwak
description: named for innkeeper pauwel kwak, who brewed his own beer. a deep amber beer w/an earthy aroma; hearty & warming

name: Baron Philippe De Rothschild
description: cadet d’oc chardonnay ’09 (france)

name: Pala
description: "i fiore" vermentino ’09 (sardegna)

name: La Fage (France)
description: cuvée centenaire côtes du roussillon 2009. grenache blanc

name: Chateau La Tarciere
description: muscadet de sèvre-et-maine sur lie ’09 (loire valley)

name: Cantele
description: primitivo ’09 (puglia)

name: Parcelles St Nicolas
description: altitude 500 ventous 2007.

name: Stefano Farina (Italia)
description: le brume langhe rosso. nebbiolo

name: Monte Oton '09
description: 100% garnacha (spain)

name: Cantele
description: negroamaro rosato ’09 (italia)

name: Tripel Karmeliet
description: golden–bronze ale w/a creamy head. inspired by the 3-grain beer of the carmelites of dendermonde in the 1600s. brewed w/raw & malted barley, wheat, oats, & house yeast. restrained hoppiness, generous spicing, fruity banana & vanilla notes. complexity & finesse

name: Hommelbier
description: m. jackson said: hoppy, golden-bronze top-fermented ale. rose-like floweriness, orange-zestiness. & a late, spicy, cumin-seed dryness. very refreshing & cleansing. try it before a meal

name: Brune 8
description: richly savory and sweet on the nose. big fruity malt palate, chocolaty malts and toffeeish sweetness. yeast and dry wood, smoke, alcohol in the finish. grows even better as it warms

name: Grand Cru
description: made by brouwerig van steenberge. brewed w/a 6-grain combo of barley, rye, spelt, wheat, maize & buckwheat w/ orange and coriander. smooth a bit sweet and easy drinking

name: Blonde
description: sunny color, slightly clovy aroma, restrained orangy fruity palate, nutty creamy texture

name: Cuvèe Des Jacobins Rouge
description: lots of tart cherry, vanilla, woody funkiness, sour apple pucker, & solid malty backing to this classic flemish sour ale

name: Gueuze Fond Tradition
description: hopleaf exclusive michael discovered while touring the brewery awhile back. very tart & authentic classic gueuze-30% wheat, 70% barley-spontaneously fermented, oak-aged to perfection

name: Framboise
description: whole fresh raspberries added to young lambic provides seasoning & sparks another fermentation, yielding great complexity. the acidity of champagne, bouquet & delicate flavor of raspberries, balanced by almondy dryness

name: BPA (Belgian Pale Ale)
description: cascade dry-hopped belgian-style pale. very foodfriendly & easy-drinking yet complex, w/notes of clove, citrus & yeast

name: Brother Thelonious
description: dark brown belgian strong ale. dark fruits, spices, caramel, brown sugar in both nose & palate. rich & mouthfilling; yeasty sweetness & alcohol, also some hop bitterness

name: Sahti
description: inspired by finnish sahti, a traditional rye ale brewed w/juniper. hazy amber ale w/sturdy mouthfeel & crisp & lively finish. brewed w/pale, crystal, rye malts & whole oats, nb’s version is bittered w/cascade and finished w/cascade & amarillo hops. juniper boughs are added to the mash; juniper berries, orange & lemon peel for festive olfactory experience

name: 1. Bodegas Atteca Old Vines 2007
description: spain (garnacha)

name: 2. Stefano Farina Le Brume Lange Rosso 2005
description: italia (nebbiolo)

name: 3. Château Haut Sarthes Bergerac 2005
description: france (merlot, cabernet, cab. franc)

name: 4. Carpineto Dogajolo 2008
description: italia (70% sangiovese, 30% cabernet sauvignon)

name: 5. Château Puynormand Montagne St. Emilion 2004
description: bordeaux (90% merlot, 10% cabernet franc)

name: 6. Colle Ticchio Cesanese Del Piglio D.O.C. 2008
description: italia

name: 7. Domaine La Garrigue Cuvée Romaine-Côtes Du Rhone 2004
description: france (60% grenache, 40% syrah)

name: 8. Domaine Monpertius Cuvée Cournoise-Vin De Pays Du Gard 2005
description: france (100% cournoise)

name: 9. Domaine Sainte Eugenie Corbieres 2005
description: france (pinot noir)

name: 11. La Valentina Montepulciano D’Abruzzo 2005
description: italia

name: 12. Les Heretiques Vin Du Pays D’Oc 2006
description: france (merlot, grenache, syrah, carignan)

name: 15. Pala Triente Cannonau Di Sardegna 2005 Italia
16. Pojer & Sandri Rosso Faye 2002
description: trentino, italia (cabernet sauvignon, cabernet franc, merlot, lagrein )

name: 17. Tamari Reserve Malbec 2006
description: mendoza, argentina

name: 18. Tenuta Della Terre Nere Etna Rosso 2008
description: italia (nerello)

name: 19. Tenuta Pederzano Lambrusco Grasparossa Di Castelvetro 2007
description: italia (served slightly chilled)

name: 20. Rioja Sierra Cantabria 2005
description: spain (tempranillo & graciano)

name: 21. Chateau Roque Le Mayne Cotes De Castillon 2002
description: bordeaux (merlot)

name: Tenuta Luisa Pino Grigio 2007
description: friuli venezia giulia, italia

name: Château Haut Sarthes Montraval Blanc 2006
description: bergerac, france (60% sauvignon blanc, 40% semillon)

name: C. D’Orschwihr Gewurztraminer "Bollennberg" 2007
description: alsace, france

name: David Duband Bourgogne Hautes Côtes De Nuits 2004
description: france (chardonnay)

name: Dom. De La Becassonne Côtes De Rhone 2007
description: france (50% roussanne, 20% claret, 30% grenache)

name: Domaine Faillenc Sainte Marie Corbières Blanc ’07
description: france (rousanne macabeu, bourblanc, clairette)

name: Domaine Pichot Vouvray 2006
description: loire valley (chenin blanc)

name: Domaine Pierre De La Grange Muscadet Sur Lie ’07
description: france

name: Grange Des Rouquette Marsanne Viognier
description: vin de pays d’oc 2006 france

name: Pierre Boniface Apremont Vin De Savoie 2007

name: Dalmore Gran Reserva
description: single malt highland whisky. the rich malty flavors tantalize the tongue, followed by marmalade and christmas cake with subtle hints of roasted coffee and chocolate. an aroma and taste of ripe oranges and lemon peel offers the elegant zesty top notes. a rich and harmonious single highland malt. matured and married in 60% sherry wood & 40% american white oak.

name: Glenmorangie Signet
description: signet has a portion of whisky in it (15-20%) made from chocolate malt. signet also contains whisky from cadboll barley malt, the first time this has been used in a glenmorangie (adding some creaminess to the whisky). the whisky is aged in a variety of casks, including sherry and new charred oak, and contains some older whiskies too up to 35 years old.

description: victot-pontfol, france

name: Ephemere
description: unibroue, quebec, canada

name: Bell’s Oarsman
description: designed as a flavorful session beer, oarsman ale uses a classic german brewing technique to impart a light, refreshing tartness. oarsman ale grew out of a desire to explore the tradition of session beers, trading intensity for finesse while still creating a worthwhile experience for the taster. the grain bill includes a healthy portion of wheat, while light hopping lend citrus & herbal notes to the aroma. bell’s brewery, kalamazoo, mi

name: Goose Island Green Line Pale Ale
description: a honey-colored, immensely sessionable american pale ale with a pronounced, bright, american hop aroma and citrus flavor. notes of biscuit and lightly toasted malt create the backbone for green line’s pleasant, crisp bitterness. goose island beer co., chicago, il

name: Goose Island Matilda
description: wild in character, with a slightly fruity aroma and a spicy yeast flavor that is as unique as it is satisfying, matilda is an intriguing choice for beer and wine lovers alike. dry and quenching, it’s the perfect accompaniment at the dining table or for casually socializing at the bar. goose island beer co., chicago, il

name: Goose Island Sofie
description: fermented with wild yeasts and aged in wine barrels with orange peel, sofie is a tart, dry, sparkling ale. a subtle, spicy white pepper note, a hint of citrus from the orange peel and a creamy vanilla finish make sofie an intriguing choice for champagne drinkers and beer drinkers who are fond of belgian saisons. goose island beer co., chicago, il

name: Half Acre Daisy Cutter
description: a west coast strong pale ale, focusing on the aromatic qualities of the hops. a master blend of 5 different hops creates a powerful nose and a dynamic flavor. half acre beer co., chicago, il

name: Hacker-Pschorr Weiss
description: hacker-pschorr weis is 100% natural and has a uniquely crisp, refreshing, smooth malty taste. brewed with pure spring water, hacker-pschorr uses a centuries-old exclusive yeast strain, hallertau hops and 60% malted and wheat barley and 40% malted barley. a clovey nose of sweet malt greets your senses and awakens your palate. hacker-pschorr brewery, munich, germany

name: New Belgium Sahti (Lips Of Faith Series)
description: inspired by finnish sahti, a traditional rye ale brewed with juniper, this sahti ale is a hazy amber ale with a sturdy mouthfeel and a crisp and lively finnish. brewed with pale, crystal, rye malts and whole oats, this version is bittered with cascade and finished with cascade and amarillo hops. juniper boughs are added to the mash and juniper berries, orange and lemon peel are pitched in the whirlpool creating a festive olfactory of citrus and juniper notes. new belgian brewing co., fort collins, co

name: Old Style
description: old style employs the traditional brewing skills of the german craftsman. kraeusened and well carbonated, old style is a beer that revives the crisp rich freshness of a classic pilsner: light in color and body, medium in aroma and bitterness, full flavored with a delicate aftertaste. milwaukee, wi

name: Three Floyds Robert The Bruce
description: a bold scottish ale with a complex malty body derived from roasted and crystal malts balanced with just the right combination of hops. this ale pours a deep ruby color, has a sweet malty nose with layered caramel and roasted notes and a full body. robust yet smooth, robert the bruce is a malt lover’s delight. three floyds brewing, munster, in

name: St-Ambroise Oatmeal Stout
description: brewed from 40 percent dark malts and roasted barley, this intensely black ale carries strong hints of espresso and chocolate. oatmeal contributes body and a long-lasting mocha-colored head to this well-hopped beer. mcauslan brewing, montréal, québec, canada

name: Stiegl
description: a noble pils of golden color with a wonderful head and an excellent clean, crisp bouquet from using only the finest saaz hops. stiegl, salzburg, austria

name: Unibroue Chambly Noire
description: like good wine, unibroue’s fine beers have flavors that develop with age. over time they become smoother, sometimes revealing notes of honey and candied fruit and developing a more assertive and lasting flavor. this phenomenon is known as "maderization" and is similar to the aging process of dessert wines like port. with its champagne-like bubbles, spices, low bitterness, and slightly chocolaty finish, noire de chambly is much milder than its appearance suggests. it’s the perfect introduction to dark ales. unibroue, montreal, canada

name: Artisan Cheese Plate
description: 10oz each, choose any three from the nine below

name: Neal's Yard Stilton
description: neal's yard dairy. nottinghamshire, england, cows milk, aged 12 to 18 weeks. one of englands creamiest stiltons with a moist firm crumbly texture and a mellow, deep and syrup flavor. a great choice with port, sherry and fall reds

name: Neal's Yard Cheddar
description: neal's yard dairy. nottinghamshire, england, raw cow milk, aged 16 months. golden-hued behemoth of intense flavor. will work with gewurtztraminc. reishing and lagers

name: Zamorano
description: castilian-leoncea. northwest madrid, spain, sheep's milk aged six months. made from uncooked pressed ewes milk. the flavor os strong and turkey. great with sherry and full-bodied wines

name: Majorero
description: canary islands, spain, goatmilk aged 60 days. pressed and uncooked, it is rubbed with oils, paprika and gotio (local wheat flour). the flavors is slightly spicy, milky, and nutty. fantastic with dry whites and bold rolls

name: Fromager D'Affiois
description: rhone alps, france, enriched cow's milk aged 2 weeks, this cheese is uncooked and unpressed and the rind is formed from white mold. smooth and creamy, this is great with red bordcaux or white burgundy

name: Ubriaco
description: fruiti venezia, gidalia italy. skimmed cow milk aged 2-3 months. ubriaco is translated as "devokeo" this is soaked in pressed grapes and wine. it is mellow, showing fruity musty flavors best with pinot noir or greek reds

name: Pecorino Toscano
